The paper discusses a new natural gradient for variational inference, which is a common technique used in machine learning and statistics. The paper also provides empirical results on classification, generative models, and matrix factorization, which are all subfields of machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also involves information theory (cs.IT) and control systems (cs.SY) to some extent, which are less likely but still possible sub-categories.
